div.innerText = "Hello";

document.body.append(div);
MINI PROJECT

CLICK COUNTER

HTML:

<button id="btn">Click</button>
<p id="count">0</p>

JS:

let count = 0;

let btn = document.querySelector("#btn");
let display = document.querySelector("#count");

btn.addEventListener("click", function() {
  count++;
  display.innerText = count;
});
QUICK SUMMARY
DOM = HTML structure as objects
JS can access and modify elements
Use querySelector for selection
innerText / innerHTML for content
style for design
addEventListener for actions
